<subSubSection pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,1086,1939]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1878,1903]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from Latin 
<taxonomicName box="[804,893,1879,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[804,893,1879,1902]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(narrow) in reference to the narrow valvae and narrow lateral lobes of vinculum in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
